text: Loleta is a census-designated place in Humboldt County, California. At the 2020 census, 828 people lived there. The town 14 meters above sea level and 24 kilometers south of Eureka. The Northwestern Pacific Railroad runs through the town, although it is abandoned. ==References== Category:Settlements in Humboldt County, California Category:Census-designated places in California
title: Loleta, California
